            "chars": "<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-1146fbad-7fff-1167-8a66-5387bfaaa013\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><em><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">HT.IV.L2</span></em></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Sissy? No</span></strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Dickens was able to &ldquo;Carry on Sissy&rdquo; and the &ldquo;power of affection&rdquo; in No. II, and in No. III he had considered possibilities for expanding her presence through either a lover or becoming acquainted with Rachael (these possibilities are left unrealized) (see <em>HT.III.L5</em> &amp; <em>HT.III.L6)</em>. Although Dickens answers this particular query about Sissy in the negative, she does make a brief appearance in the &lsquo;number&rsquo; in chapter 25 when Louisa returns to Coketown to visit her dying mother. In that scene, Mrs. Gradgrind gestures at the &ldquo;power of affection&rdquo; that Sissy embodies to direct Louisa beyond her father&rsquo;s philosophy: &ldquo;&lsquo;But there is something&ndash;not an Ology at all&ndash;that your father has missed, or forgotten, Louisa. I don&rsquo;t know what it is. I have often sat with Sissy near me, and thought about it&rsquo;&rdquo; (HT 225). </span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>"
        }
    ],
